Pancreatic pseudocyst with biliary fistula: treatment with endoscopic internal drainage. Surgical drainage is the standard treatment for pancreatic pseudocysts and their complications. However, acute symptomatic pancreatic pseudocysts are amenable to endoscopic internal drainage in select cases. We report a case of pancreatic pseudocyst with biliary fistula resulting from a recurrent pseudocyst treated with endoscopic stent drainage.